WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
Maybe King lives in the Bahamas.

00:05.000 --> 00:12.000
She's 13 years old and likes pop music, reading and swimming.

00:12.000 --> 00:16.000
Her mother and father are doctors.

00:16.000 --> 00:20.000
They work at the Supreme Court Animal Hospital.

00:20.000 --> 00:23.000
The hospital is next to their home.

00:23.000 --> 00:26.000
A blue house by the sea.

00:27.000 --> 00:32.000
It's very old, but it's beautiful and maybe loves it.

00:32.000 --> 00:35.000
Her grandfather loves it too.

00:35.000 --> 00:38.000
He lives with the family.

00:42.000 --> 00:49.000
On Saturdays, Maisie and her grandfather often go out in his boat, the warm wind.

00:49.000 --> 00:55.000
Maisie likes to swim underwater and look at all the beautiful fish.

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
One day, she sees something.

00:59.000 --> 01:02.000
It's a piece of wood.

01:02.000 --> 01:04.000
There are some letters on it.

01:04.000 --> 01:09.000
M-N-A.

01:09.000 --> 01:13.000
What can that be? Maisie fakes.

01:13.000 --> 01:19.000
I know. I can ask Grandad.

01:19.000 --> 01:22.000
She swims back to the warm wind.

01:22.000 --> 01:27.000
Grandad, there's a big piece of wood.

01:27.000 --> 01:30.000
But her grandfather isn't listening.

01:30.000 --> 01:37.000
He's watching a big, expensive American boat and a dolphin.

01:37.000 --> 01:40.000
Oh, no, he says.

01:40.000 --> 01:43.000
That boat's going too fast.

01:43.000 --> 01:46.000
The driver can't see the dolphin.

01:46.000 --> 01:48.000
Hey!

01:49.000 --> 01:52.000
But it's too late.

01:52.000 --> 01:58.000
The boat hits the dolphin and drives away.

02:01.000 --> 02:04.000
Maisie's very angry.

02:04.000 --> 02:09.000
She and her grandfather take the dolphin back to Freeport.

02:09.000 --> 02:12.000
Her mother's in the garden.

02:12.000 --> 02:16.000
She says, what have you got there?

02:17.000 --> 02:19.000
A dolphin?

02:19.000 --> 02:22.000
Maisie says, yes.

02:22.000 --> 02:25.000
Can you and Dad help him?

02:25.000 --> 02:30.000
Then she sees the big American boat.

02:30.000 --> 02:34.000
Why is that here, Joff?

02:34.000 --> 02:39.000
Her mother says, there's an American in the house with Dad.

02:39.000 --> 02:41.000
Carl Flint.

02:41.000 --> 02:44.000
I think it's his boat.

02:45.000 --> 02:48.000
Maisie runs into the house.

02:48.000 --> 02:51.000
She can hear her father.

02:51.000 --> 03:01.000
He's saying, you want to give me $200,000 for the hospital and this house?

03:01.000 --> 03:05.000
Carl Flint says, yes.

03:05.000 --> 03:10.000
I want to build a big hotel here.

03:10.000 --> 03:14.000
Maisie's father thinks for a moment.

03:14.000 --> 03:23.000
Well, the hospital isn't doing very well, but I need a little time.

03:23.000 --> 03:30.000
Carl Flint says to him, okay, you've got four weeks.

03:30.000 --> 03:36.000
That night, Maisie looks out of her bedroom window.

03:36.000 --> 03:41.000
She can see the dolphin in a big pool next to the hospital.

03:41.000 --> 03:46.000
She thinks, he needs a name.

03:46.000 --> 03:51.000
I know Ben.

03:51.000 --> 03:53.000
Then she looks at the moon.

03:53.000 --> 03:59.000
She says, Carl Flint carved by this house.

03:59.000 --> 04:02.000
It's our home.

04:02.000 --> 04:05.000
She feels very sad.

04:05.000 --> 04:16.000
Then she looks at the dolphin again, says, good night, Ben, and closes her window.

04:16.000 --> 04:22.000
The next day, Maisie goes to see Ben after school.

04:22.000 --> 04:27.000
She asks her mother, how is he?

04:27.000 --> 04:32.000
Mrs. King looks at the long red line on the dolphin's head.

04:32.000 --> 04:37.000
He isn't eating, she says.

04:37.000 --> 04:42.000
There are a lot of fish in a bucket next to the pool.

04:42.000 --> 04:49.000
Maisie takes one out and says, this is for you, Ben.

04:49.000 --> 04:53.000
The dolphin eats the fish.

04:53.000 --> 04:56.000
Maisie's mother is very happy.

04:56.000 --> 05:00.000
She says, that's good.

05:00.000 --> 05:09.000
He likes you.

05:09.000 --> 05:14.000
Three weeks later, Ben's strong and well again.

05:14.000 --> 05:17.000
You may be a friend.

05:17.000 --> 05:22.000
She plays games and swims within every day.

05:22.000 --> 05:30.000
One evening, Mrs. King says, oh John, I don't want to make Maisie unhappy.

05:30.000 --> 05:34.000
But, John King looks at her.

05:34.000 --> 05:38.000
I know, he says, Ben's well now.

05:38.000 --> 05:42.000
His home's back in the sea.

05:42.000 --> 05:46.000
Maisie's grandfather says, it's okay.

05:46.000 --> 05:50.000
Let me talk to her.

05:50.000 --> 05:55.000
Later, Maisie and her grandfather watch the sun go down.

05:55.000 --> 06:01.000
Tomorrow, Maisie's eyes are very sad.

06:01.000 --> 06:07.000
But grandad, Ben's my friend. Can't I?

06:07.000 --> 06:10.000
I'm sorry, Maisie.

06:10.000 --> 06:15.000
Her grandfather says, but your dolphin's well again.

06:15.000 --> 06:19.000
It's time for him to go home.

06:19.000 --> 06:24.000
I'm losing everything, Maisie thinks.

06:24.000 --> 06:32.000
First my home, now Ben.

06:32.000 --> 06:38.000
The next day, Maisie and her grandfather take Ben out to sea.

06:38.000 --> 06:46.000
At half past ten, grandad stops the warm wind.

06:46.000 --> 06:52.000
Inside of the boat, Maisie puts one hand on the dolphin's head.

06:52.000 --> 06:58.000
Goodbye, she says, please don't forget me.

06:58.000 --> 07:05.000
Ben, she cuts two thick ropes and Ben swims away.

07:05.000 --> 07:13.000
Okay, grandad asks, for a moment Maisie can't speak.

07:13.000 --> 07:16.000
She answers.

07:16.000 --> 07:21.000
Yes, okay.

07:21.000 --> 07:29.000
They start to go home. Maisie's very sad and doesn't say anything.

07:29.000 --> 07:33.000
Then, two minutes later, she stands up.

07:33.000 --> 07:38.000
Stop, grandad, stop the boat.

07:38.000 --> 07:42.000
She can see a dolphin beside them in the water.

07:42.000 --> 07:51.000
It's Ben, and he's got something in his mouth.

07:51.000 --> 07:56.000
What's he got there, grandad asks.

07:56.000 --> 08:00.000
Maisie says, I cannot see.

08:00.000 --> 08:03.000
It's not very big.

08:03.000 --> 08:06.000
Is it an old key?

08:06.000 --> 08:10.000
Grandad stops the warm wind.

08:10.000 --> 08:14.000
Now, Ben's jumping out of the water.

08:14.000 --> 08:19.000
Why is he doing that, grandad asks.

08:19.000 --> 08:24.000
Maisie says, I think he wants me to follow him.

08:24.000 --> 08:28.000
Please, can I?

08:28.000 --> 08:31.000
The old man looks at her.

08:31.000 --> 08:36.000
You two and your games, he says.

08:36.000 --> 08:40.000
Okay, but only for five minutes.

08:40.000 --> 08:44.000
Oh, grandad, thank you.

08:44.000 --> 08:46.000
Says Maisie.

08:46.000 --> 08:53.000
Five minutes later, she jumps over the side of the warm wind.

08:53.000 --> 09:05.000
Under the water, Maisie sees a piece of wood with the letters N, N,

09:05.000 --> 09:09.000
A on it.

09:09.000 --> 09:13.000
I don't remember this, she thinks.

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
But Ben doesn't stop there.

09:16.000 --> 09:20.000
He swims between two big stones.

09:20.000 --> 09:23.000
Then they come to a box.

09:23.000 --> 09:28.000
It has the word Montoya on the top.

09:28.000 --> 09:34.000
Maisie takes the key from Ben's mouth and opens the box.

09:35.000 --> 09:39.000
There are lots of gold coins in it.

09:39.000 --> 09:44.000
Thousands of them.

09:44.000 --> 09:49.000
The next morning Maisie's name is in the newspaper.

09:49.000 --> 09:56.000
The story says, three-port girl finds Spanish gold.

09:56.000 --> 10:01.000
Mr. King telephones Carl Flint in New York.

10:02.000 --> 10:04.000
Ah, hello.

10:04.000 --> 10:06.000
Says Carl Flint.

10:06.000 --> 10:09.000
Do you have an answer for me?

10:09.000 --> 10:11.000
Yes, I do.

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
Says Maisie's father.

10:13.000 --> 10:15.000
And it's no.

10:15.000 --> 10:19.000
We don't want to sell the house or the hospital.

10:19.000 --> 10:23.000
Goodbye, Mr. Flint.

10:23.000 --> 10:30.000
With the money from the Montoya coins, Maisie's mother and father build a new hospital.

10:30.000 --> 10:33.000
They're very happy.

10:33.000 --> 10:36.000
Maisie's happy too.

10:36.000 --> 10:39.000
Oh, Grandad.

10:39.000 --> 10:42.000
She says one evening in the garden.

10:42.000 --> 10:54.000
Now we can always live here because of, at that moment, Ben jumps out of the sea.

10:54.000 --> 10:56.000
Ben!

10:56.000 --> 10:59.000
The old man and the girl laugh.

10:59.000 --> 11:04.000
Then the sun goes down and they walk back to the house.

